      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEVIL'S SYMPATHY (5) has a strong record this track and trip with six wins and four placings from 17 starts. Missed the frame latest (25.67) when seventh over 450m at Warrnambool in a Grade 4/5. Rates on top and should go close. IAN ALBERT (1) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fifth (30.35) in a Free For All at Sandown. Goes very well here at the trip finding the frame in each of six starts. Better than last start and can bounce back. DR. FANATICAL (8) turned in a plain performance last time when fifth at Traralgon over 570m behind Paw Manny (33.74) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Leading chance. DR. LEVIATE (7) boasts a solid strike-rate over this trip.",
